addController(address).details: Emits `ControllerAdded(controller)` after adding the `controller` to the `controllers` mapping.

params.controller: The address of the new controller.

params.baseNode_: The node that this contract manages registrations for.
params.collectionURI_: The URI for the collection's metadata.
params.owner_: The permissioned address initialized as the `owner` in the `Ownable` context.
params.tokenURI_: The base token URI for NFT metadata.

params.id: The id of the name to check availability of.

returns._0: `true` if the name is available, else `false`.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Names become unowned when their registration expires.

params.tokenId: The id of the name to query the owner of.

returns._0: address The address currently marked as the owner of the given token ID.

params.duration: Duration in seconds for the registration.
params.id: The token id determined by keccak256(label).
params.owner: The address that should own the registration.
params.resolver: Address of the resolver for the name.

removeController(address).details: Emits `ControllerRemoved(controller)` after removing the `controller` from the `controllers` mapping.

params.controller: The address of the controller to remove.

params.duration: The time that will be added to this name's expiry.
params.id: The id of the name to renew.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setContractURI(string).details: Allows the owner to set the the contract Uniform Resource Identifier (URI)`.     Emits the `ContractURIUpdated` event.

params.resolver: The address of the new resolver contract.

setTokenURI(string).details: Allows the owner to set the the base Uniform Resource Identifier (URI)`.     Emits the `BatchMetadataUpdate` event for the full range of valid `tokenIds`.

params.interfaceID: the ERC165 iface id being checked for compliance

returns._0: bool Whether this contract supports the provided interfaceID

tokenURI(uint256).details: Reverts if the `tokenId` has not be registered.

params.tokenId: The token for which to return the metadata uri.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addController(address).notice: Authorises a controller, who can register and renew domains.

baseNode().notice: The namehash of the TLD this registrar owns (eg, .lit).

constructor.notice: BaseRegistrar constructor used to initialize the configuration of the implementation.

contractURI().notice: Returns the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for the contract.

controllers(address).notice: A map of addresses that are authorised to register and renew names.

isAvailable(uint256).notice: Returns true if the specified name is available for registration.

nameExpires(bytes32).notice: A map of expiry times to node.

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Gets the owner of the specified token ID.

registerWithRecord(uint256,address,uint2.notice: Register a name and add details to the record in the Registry.

removeController(address).notice: Revoke controller permission for an address.

renew(uint256,uint256).notice: Allows holders of names to renew their ownerhsip and extend their expiry.

setResolver(address).notice: Set the resolver for the node this registrar manages.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: ERC165 compliant signal for interface support.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for token `id`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: transferFrom is overridden to handle the registry update.
